<title type="html"><![CDATA[1/16(Sat.)Being married doesn't necessarily make you happier than staying single, finds new study/GAME NIGHT FUN(Mei)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=465&amp;p=483#p483"><![CDATA[
1/16(Sat.)Being married doesn't necessarily make you happier than staying single, finds new study/GAME NIGHT FUN(Mei)<br /><br /><br />#1<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://sg.news.yahoo.com/being-married-doesnt-necessarily-happier-staying-single-finds-114042625.html">https://sg.news.yahoo.com/being-married ... 42625.html</a><!-- m --><br />Host :Mei<br /><br />Questions:<br />1. Traditionally we believe &quot;people often think that they need to be married to be happy.&quot; However, this new study finding is opposite: Being married doesn't make you happier than staying single. What do you think about the result of the study? Or why single people can have a happy life?<br /><br />2.The researcher said that &quot;if you're unhappy to begin with, getting married is not likely to drastically change that.'' Do you agree with this quote and why? <br /><br />3.If you are a parent, would you encourage your children to get married? Or what goes through your mind when your parents ask you to get married?<br /><br />4.Taiwanese and other countries' governments have taken actions and set incentives to increase marriage rate and birth rate, do you agree with that and why? <br /><br />5. If the study result gets published widely on media, what trends or thoughts will happen to younger generation?<br /><br />Optional topic:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZZZ6QB5TSfk">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZZZ6QB5TSfk</a><!-- m --><br /><br />#2 <br /><br />GAME NIGHT FUN !!!<br />We will play Taboo game (modified) this coming Saturday night!!!  <br />Come to have fun, exercise your brain, and of course practice your English skills! All challengers are most welcome!<br /><br /><br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 ~ 7:30 pm greetings &amp; free talk<br />7:30 ~ 8:15 pm guests introduced &amp; first session discussion<br />8:15 ~ 8:45 pm presentation, sharing the article &amp; other experiences<br />8:45 ~ 9:30 pm second session discussion<br /><br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven,<br />板橋民生路二段237 號,<br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30,<br /><br />P.S.<br />1.因聚會地點是在咖啡店內，所以有低消80元喔！<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交1000元 (學生:500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Thu Jan 14, 2021 1:22 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
